CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1781486246
OL,3,CScientists make new discovery about
OL,4,Cthe history of the Giant's Causeway
OL,6,FDr Simon Tapster, geochronologist at
OL,7,Fthe British Geological Survey (BGS),
OL,8,Fsaid: "Fundamentally, what we've done
OL,9,Fis by piecing together this tapestry
OL,10,Fof volcanic rocks all across the North
OL,11,FAtlantic, but focusing on Northern
OL,12,FIreland, we have been able to reassess
OL,13,Fa major globally impacting volcanic
OL,14,Fevent.
OL,16,F"In doing that, and in reassessing the
OL,17,Ftimescales, we have shown that
OL,18,Factually it occurred in a much shorter
OL,19,Fduration."
OL,26,@pD@GOUxD@AOU{D@JO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
